    <note>Nie(1) Yong [1380] His son Zhen's [3682] son-in-law was Li(2) Hang's [8076] and Li(2) Wei(3)'s [7042] nephew. Zhen's wife, born L?1), gave birth to five daughters who all married distinguished members of the bureaucratic elite (shidafu). The youngest was married to Hao(1) Yin [3333], originally a Shizhou, Dinghu resident who apparently moved to Caizhou. Hao(1) Yin came from a poor family, worked hard to support his parents and earned the jinshi degree and was appointed Xingguo jun, Tongshan xian magistrate in 1063. Their son-in-law was Dong(1) Shen [1740]. Fan Zuyu, WJ, 43.9b-12a; XCB, 21.6b, 23.12a-13a.</note>
